HEADWORD: Clicker
<hw>Click"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
stands before a shop door to invite people to buy.</def> <mark>[Low,
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Print.)</fld> <def>One who as has charge of the
work of a companionship.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clicket</ent>⟦br⟧
